LEGAL AUTO CLAIMS INSURANCE POLICY

BETWEEN AMERICAN FAMILY INSURANCE AND BRENDA PARKER 

This Auto Insurance Policy (The "Policy") entered into by and between the Insurer, AMERICAN FAMILY INSURANCE, herein referred to as "the Insurer", and the Named Insured, BRENDA PARKER, herein referred to as "the Insured?. This policy agreement applies to the following Vehicle: 1981 Honda CR-X

Policy Number: 709c8325-5fe2-47b4-9e59-e211309d9150

Policy Term: Start Date: October 10, 1978 End Date: June 18, 1993

Premium: 79899.00

Contact Information:
Christopher Henry
73749 Hayden Avenue
South Wayne, AL 86106

Underwriting Company: The United Services Automobile Association (USAA)

AUTOMOBILE LIABILITY INSURANCE

The Insurer agrees to pay all sums that the Insured becomes legally obligated to pay as damages because of bodily injury or property damage caused by an auto accident. This coverage applies only to liability assumed by the Insured under a written contract, other than a contract of carriage.

Limits of Liability: 
The Insurer will pay damages for bodily injury, sickness, disease or death of up to $50,000 per person and $100,000 per occurrence and property damage up to $50,000.

Exclusion: 
This coverage does not cover damages resulting from wars, invasion and insurrections, rebellion, revolution, hostilities or civil war, or any hostile acts by or against a government or sovereign power (including the United States).

WHAT IS NOT COVERED:

This coverage does not apply to:
1. Damages arising out of the ownership, operation, maintenance, loading or unloading of motor vehicles while in or upon any railroad, bridge, or railroad or bridge approach.

2. Damages for loss caused by or resulting from the discharge or escape of steam or water in the boiler, machinery or equipment of vehicles subject to the provisions of the Steam Boiler Inspection Acts of the United States.

3. Damages caused by or resulting from vehicles owned or operated by insureds engaged in war-time reenactment activities or as owners.

AUTOMOBILE MEDICAL PAYMENTS

The Insurer agrees to pay all reasonable medical expenses incurred within 3 years of an accident for necessary medical services, surgical care, x-ray examinations, dental services, and prosthetic devices, which are incurred by the Insured and/or passengers.

Limits of Liability: 
The Insured and/or passengers may recover up to $2000.00 for necessary medical care.

Exclusion: 
Medical payments coverage is not available for expenses incurred for services performed by any person who is a member of the Insured's household.

WHAT IS NOT COVERED: 

This coverage does not apply to:
1. Any medical expenses incurred for injuries sustained by the Insured or passengers while occupying a vehicle that is owned by the Insured or a member of the Insured's household and is not described in the policy.

2. Any medical expenses incurred for injuries sustained by the Insured or passengers while occupying a vehicle operated by a for-hire driver.

3. Any medical expenses incurred for injuries sustained by the Insured or passengers while occupying a vehicle used principally for the transportation of persons or property for hire or for fee.

4. Any medical expenses incurred for injuries sustained by the Insured or passengers while occupying a vehicle owned by the Insured or a member of the Insured's household and operated by a federal, state, or local government employee in the scope of their employment.

AUTOMOBILE DEBT INDEMNITY INSURANCE

The Insurer agrees to pay all sums which the Insured is legally obligated to pay for the following:
a) For damage to or loss of covered property.

b) For liability assumed by the Insured under a contract of indebtedness or warranty in connection with the sale, lease or financing of a motor vehicle described in the policy.

Limits of Liability:
The Insurer will pay the amount of damages caused to covered property in an amount not exceeding $100,000 for any one accident.

Exclusion:
This coverage does not apply to motor vehicles that are not described in the policy, or vehicles with liability coverage that exceeds the policy limits.
